description: Maharashtra CM Devendra Fadnavis dismissed claims of his potential PM candidacy in 2029, reaffirming Narendra Modi as BJP's leader. He countered remarks by Sanjay Raut regarding Modi's retirement and defended the National Education Policy amid criticisms by Sonia Gandhi, emphasizing the need for Indianizing the education system.
title: Devendra Fadnavis trashes Raut's claim on PM Modi's 'looming retirement'

description: India and the US are set to begin their major tri-service exercise 'Tiger Triumph' in the Bay of Bengal, focusing on military interoperability for humanitarian assistance and disaster relief. The exercise includes operations at Visakhapatnam and Kakinada, with India deploying warships, aircraft, and troops, while the US contributes amphibious warships and marines.
title: India, US to kick off tri-service exercise in Bay of Bengal today

description: The Kerala Catholic Bishops Council (KCBC) urges all MPs from Kerala to back the Waqf Amendment Bill, gaining support from the BJP and finance minister Nirmala Sitharaman. Congress criticises the move, suggesting it reflects undue interference. The bill aims for transparent management of waqf properties.
title: Kerala Bishops' backing for waqf bill big boost for BJP

description: Iran has lodged a complaint with the United Nations Security Council, condemning US President Donald Trump’s threats of military action and describing them as a violation of international law. Iran warns it will respond decisively to any aggression. This follows Trump’s warning of severe bombing if Iran does not agree to a new nuclear deal.
title: 'Reckless, belligerent': Iran complains about Donald Trump's threat to UN

description: Senior RSS leader Suresh 'Bhaiyyaji' Joshi stated that the issue of Aurangzeb's tomb in Maharashtra was raised unnecessarily and highlighted the inclusiveness of Bharat by referencing Shivaji's respect for even Afzal Khan. Meanwhile, CM Devendra Fadnavis opposed the tomb's glorification but noted it is an ASI-protected site. Tensions continue with recent violence following VHP's actions against the tomb.
title: Row over Aurangzeb's tomb unnecessary: RSS
RSS members can join Kashi, Mathura campaigns: Dattatreya Hosabale

description: E-commerce ads claiming instant skin whitening by lotions have been proven unsubstantiated, as companies admitted to exaggerating unique selling points to stand out online. The Central Consumer Protection Authority has fined these companies and warned of harsher penalties for future offences, emphasizing the illegality of misleading advertisements.
title: 3 lotion companies fail to prove 'skin whitening' claims, fined

description: Uttarakhand chief minister Pushkar Singh Dhami announced the renaming of 13 areas and two roads in four districts to reflect Indian culture and heritage. The changes include new names in Haridwar, Dehradun, Nainital, and Udham Singh Nagar, inspired by prominent Indian figures.
title: Aurangzebpur to be renamed Shivaji Nagar, says Uttarakhand CM Dhami

description: A historic colonial-era structure, Mahafezkhana, has been demolished by the Guwahati Metropolitan Development Authority to facilitate the Brahmaputra riverfront expansion. The heritage building, which withstood major earthquakes in 1897 and 1950, was demolished despite public outcry and suggestions for its preservation.
title: Heritage structure razed to make way for Guwahati riverfront project

description: The Delhi High Court ruled that individuals with HIV cannot be denied employment or promotion, emphasizing the obligation for 'reasonable accommodation.' It ordered the CAPF to review the cases of three personnel denied promotions or appointments due to their HIV status, stating such denials violate the HIV Act and are discriminatory.
title: HIV+ status no ground to deny CAPF job or promotion: High court

description: CISF has initiated the 'Great Indian Coastal Cyclothon' to raise awareness about coastal security by engaging with coastal communities. The event concluded with 125 cyclists, including 14 women, covering 6,553 km over 25 days and connecting with 58 communities across 11 states and UTs, reaching a 2.5 crore-strong audience.
title: In coastal outreach, CISF holds 6,500km cyclothon

description: The Indian government has dismissed a New York Times report alleging Hindustan Aeronautics Limited's involvement in transferring sensitive British technology to Russia as inaccurate and misleading. Officials emphasize that the Indian entity adhered to all international trade obligations and laws, highlighting the need for reputable media to ensure accuracy before publication.
title: India junks NYT claim of HAL transferring sensitive tech to Russia

description: Khar police visited comedian Kunal Kamra's Mahim home to investigate his remarks about Maharashtra deputy CM Eknath Shinde in a recent show. Kamra criticized this action as a waste of resources, and he currently resides in Puducherry. Police have begun recording statements from audience members.
title: Kunal Kamra show audience members served notices

description: The 170-year-old Nakhasa Bazaar in Kashipur, known for trading rare horse breeds, has been canceled due to land unavailability. The fair, established in 1855, has drawn traders from across India. This abrupt closure marks the end of an era for the region’s cultural and commercial heritage.
title: Land not available, Kashipur's historic horse market shuts down

description: Qari Abdul Rehman, a member of the banned anti-Shia outfit ASWJ, was killed in a targeted attack by masked assailants in Karachi's Qaid Abad. The incident, believed to be sectarian in nature, has heightened concerns over Pakistan's sectarian violence. The ASWJ condemned the act as terrorism.
title: Member of banned anti-Shia outfit ASWJ killed in targeted attack in Pakistan

description: The US Department of Energy has granted regulatory clearance for Holtec International to transfer small modular reactor technology to India, partnering with Indian firms. This approval marks significant progress in the Indo-US Civil Nuclear Agreement, potentially leading to the construction of US-designed nuclear reactors in India.
title: Nearly 20 years after N-deal, DoE clears US firm to build & design reactors in India

description: Reimbursements to private hospitals under the Central Government Health Scheme (CGHS) have surged from 24% in 2019-20 to 60% in 2023-24. A significant rise in the number of beneficiaries has driven this increase. Instances of fraudulent billing and overcharging by empanelled hospitals have raised concerns about proper oversight and cost-effectiveness in the scheme.
title: Private hospitals' share in CGHS spend up from 24% to 60% in 4 years
Public interest overrides reputation in mass petitions: High court
100% tariff from India, 700% from Japan: White House shows receipts ahead of 'Liberation Day'

description: Nidhi Tewari, a 2014-batch Indian Foreign Service officer, has been appointed as private secretary to PM Narendra Modi. This marks a significant achievement as she becomes the first woman to secure this position in recent history, bringing valuable experience from her roles in the PMO and foreign ministry.
title: 2014-batch IFS officer Nidhi Tewari named private secretary to PM Modi

description: The upcoming April-June season is predicted to experience hotter than normal temperatures across most of India, with an increase in heatwave days. Vulnerable populations are at higher risk of heat-related illnesses, and anticipatory actions by local authorities are advised to mitigate potential impacts.
title: April-June likely to be hotter than usual across India: IMD

description: EPFO is proposing to increase the auto settlement limit for its subscribers from Rs 1 lakh to Rs 5 lakh, pending approval by the central board of trustees. The organisation has already streamlined the claim process significantly, resulting in faster settlements and an expected record of over 6 crore settlements this year.
title: EPFO eyes raising auto-settlement limit to Rs 5 lakh
Elon Musk's 'baby mama' Ashley St Clair sells her Tesla: 'I am not the only one...'

description: A fresh encounter between terrorists and security forces erupted in Jammu and Kashmir's Kathua, with three terrorists trapped. Following previous clashes that resulted in casualties, security forces have intensified search operations with aerial surveillance and sniffer dogs. Deputy Inspector General Shiv Kumar Sharma emphasized the commitment to the mission until the last terrorist is neutralized.
title: Fresh encounter breaks out in J&K's Kathua, 3 terrorists trapped

description: A sweeping crackdown by the Trump administration is targeting foreign students across US campuses, using AI surveillance, visa revocations, and ideological screening to punish perceived dissent. Under the banner of combating antisemitism and restoring “order,” the government is pushing universities to police speech, dismantle academic programs, and comply with politically charged demands—or risk devastating funding cuts. International students, once welcomed as scholars, now face detention, deportation, and digital monitoring for mere activism or online expression. What began as policy enforcement has become a full-scale reengineering of academic freedom, immigration norms, and the soul of US higher education.
title: From ambush arrests to self-deport: How Trump is threatening foreign students

description: ChatGPT's Ghibli image generator has taken social media by storm, leading to increased user engagement and positivity online. OpenAI CEO Sam Altman expressed his delight at the positive response, despite earlier tensions with Elon Musk over OpenAI's direction and ownership restructuring.
title: OpenAI CEO Sam Altman calls Elon Musk's Twitter 'negative platform'

description: Five months after a bank burglary in Karnataka's Davanagere district, police have arrested six first-time offenders. The mastermind, Vijay Kumar from Madurai, extensively planned the heist by watching crime dramas and documentaries. Motivated by a rejected loan application, they looted 17.7kg of gold worth nearly Rs 16 crore.
title: Taking lessons from Money Heist, 6 loot gold from SBI branch in Karnataka

description: A US court dismissed Gurpatwant Singh Pannun's claim of delivering a summons to NSA Ajit Doval during PM Modi's US visit. The court confirmed the summons wasn't served properly as required, aligning with India's stance. The incident involved attempted delivery by process servers which failed due to Secret Service intervention.
title: US Secret Service nixed Pannun plan to serve Pankaj Doval summons

description: At least seven people, including four children and two women, lost their lives in a gas cylinder explosion in West Bengal's South 24 Parganas district. The incident occurred in a house in Dholaghat village around 9 pm. Another woman sustained injuries and was taken to the hospital. Authorities believe firecrackers stored in the house ignited, causing the explosion.
title: West Bengal: 7 killed, 1 injured in gas cylinder blast in South 24 Parganas

description: Mumbai Indians made IPL history by becoming the first team to win 10 matches against a single opponent at one venue, defeating Kolkata Knight Riders at Wankhede Stadium. MI restricted KKR to 116 runs, with Ashwani Kumar taking four wickets. Ryan Rickelton and Suryakumar Yadav led the chase, securing an eight-wicket victory with over seven overs remaining.
title: MI create history, set IPL record for most wins against a team at one venue

description: Shashi Tharoor praises PM Modi for India's vaccine diplomacy  contrasting with past criticism from Congress leaders like Rahul and Sonia Gandhi. Tharoor's remarks have embarrassed his party, giving BJP an opportunity to mock Congress. BJP welcomes these acknowledgments of Modi's successful global initiatives.
title: Tharoor jabs Congress yet again, praises PM Modi's vaccine diplomacy

description: The Trump White House directed Department of Government Efficiency employees to disable Signal's auto-delete feature to preserve records, following revelations of sensitive military information leaks. Officials mistakenly included an Atlantic reporter in the Signal chats discussing Yemen attack plans, prompting the new policy to ensure compliance with federal recordkeeping laws.
title: White House to DOGE employees: Disable this feature of Signal app

description: Mumbai Indians' pacer Ashwani Kumar impressed everyone with his 4/24 on an IPL debut, leading his team to an eight-wicket victory against Kolkata Knight Riders. Ashwani's performance was instrumental in bundling KKR out for 116, marking him as a promising future talent. KKR’s innings started on a disastrous note as Sunil Narine was bowled for a duck by Trent Boult in the very first over. The collapse continued when Quinton de Kock (1) followed in the next over, caught by Ashwani off Deepak Chahar.
title: Ashwani's record-breaking debut powers MI to first win of IPL 2025

description: China's CIBR and NeuCyber are aiming to implant brain chips in 13 individuals by the end of the year, with plans for significant expansions in 2026. The Beinao No.1 chip has already demonstrated potential in paralyzed patients, positioning China to challenge the US in brain-computer interface advancements.
title: China's state-owned firm poised to surpass US in brain chip race

description: During a rally in Wisconsin, Tesla CEO Elon Musk was interrupted by a protester while discussing death threats. Musk accused George Soros of funding protests against Tesla. He countered the disruption with humor and chants of 'USA.' Musk also supported Republican Brad Schimel by offering financial incentives for petition signers against 'activist' judges.
title: Elon Musk at Wisconsin rally: 'Say hi to Soros for me', making crowd chant ...

description: Mumbai Indians' 23-year-old debutant Ashwani Kumar had a stellar start to his IPL career, taking four wickets against Kolkata Knight Riders. Despite pre-match nerves, he delivered an impressive performance, helping bundle out KKR for 116. Kumar credited captain Hardik Pandya for strategic advice and expressed pride in his achievement. This was his first four-wicket haul in any format.
title: 'I just had a banana ...': Ashwani reveals after record-breaking IPL debut
Jailed Pakistan former PM Imran Khan nominated for Nobel peace prize

description: The Trump administration predicts a "golden age" for US-India relations despite failing to finalize a bilateral trade agreement. Discussions continue on easing tariffs and addressing immigration issues. Significant concessions from India include cutting tariffs on various US imports, aiming for a balanced trade relationship.
title: 'No exceptions': Trump says reciprocal tariffs will be imposed on all countries from April 2

description: Peter Schrager, a popular figure from Good Morning Football, confirmed his departure from NFL Network with plans rumored towards joining ESPN. This move could be indicative of a significant media shift, particularly with whispers of ESPN potentially acquiring NFL Network. Schrager's expertise and presence make him a valuable asset for future NFL coverage.
title: Peter Schrager’s surprise NFL network exit for ESPN

description: Shashi Tharoor praises PM Modi for India's vaccine diplomacy  contrasting with past criticism from Congress leaders like Rahul and Sonia Gandhi. Tharoor's remarks have embarrassed his party, giving BJP an opportunity to mock Congress. BJP welcomes these acknowledgments of Modi's successful global initiatives.
title: Tharoor praises Modi govt's vaccine diplomacy; Cong had called it 'PR tactics'

description: Mumbai Indians' Ashwani Kumar had an incredible IPL debut, taking 4 for 24 against Kolkata Knight Riders, the best by an Indian on IPL debut. His efforts helped restrict KKR to the lowest total of this IPL season. The 23-year-old's outstanding performance, combined with Deepak Chahar's contribution, highlights his promising future.
title: Ashwani Kumar scripts history with record-breaking IPL debut for MI

description: Thai authorities are investigating the collapse of a 30-storey office tower in Bangkok after a powerful earthquake in Myanmar. The building's design, construction, and material standards are under scrutiny, with substandard steel possibly contributing to the disaster. Rescue operations continue as concerns over Thailand’s building safety regulations and emergency response system persist.
title: Design, material? Thailand probes why Chinese-built tower collapsed in quake
'I want my PhD': Indian student hopes Columbia will take her back

description: NASA astronauts Sunita Williams and Butch Wilmore discussed their nine-month extended stay on the ISS due to technical issues with Boeing's Starliner spacecraft. They adapted to the situation, focusing on their mission, while their return was facilitated by NASA and SpaceX amid external political pressures.
title: 'Is Nasa to blame?' What Sunita, Butch said on delayed return from space

description: Trump’s 25% tariff on imported vehicles aids Tesla in the US but fails against China’s BYD, which leads global EV sales. Tesla faces backlash abroad due to Musk’s Trump affiliation, impacting its brand. Chinese EV competitors like BYD, XPeng, Nio are advancing rapidly. Future competition hinges not just on tariffs but technological and market dynamics.
title: 'Moment of truth for Musk': Can Trump's auto tariffs save Tesla from BYD?

description: A family's Eid celebration in Delhi turned tragic when their two-year-old daughter was fatally hit by a car driven by a neighbor's teenage son in Paharganj. The incident, captured on CCTV, showed the child being run over as the car moved forward hesitantly. The toddler was pronounced dead at a nearby medical facility.
title: On cam: Two-yr-old girl crushed under car being driven by teen in Delhi

description: Rocket Mortgage is set to acquire Mr. Cooper in an all-stock deal valued at $9.4 billion, soon after acquiring Redfin. The merger will handle one in six US mortgages, adding 7 million clients to Rocket's portfolio. Jay Bray will become President and CEO of the combined company, expected to boost loan volumes and reduce customer acquisition costs.
title: Rocket Companies to acquire Mr Cooper in $9.4 billion all-stock deal

description: Russia's Supreme Court is set to consider removing the Taliban from its terrorist organization list on April 17, following a recommendation from the prosecutor general's office. The move comes as Russia continues to engage diplomatically with the Taliban despite their terrorist classification since 2003.
title: Russia to rule on removing Taliban from 'terror' list after 20 years
Why Trump's 'maximum pressure' tactic against Iran is a worry for India

description: Several international students in the U.S. face arrests and deportation for participating in pro-Palestinian protests and allegedly supporting Hamas. Notable cases include Tufts University's Rumeysa Ozturk, Columbia's Mahmoud Khalil, and Georgetown's Badar Khan Suri. Each faces legal battles amid accusations, with varied backgrounds and alleged activities.
title: Trump's crackdown on pro-Palestinian protests: Who are the int students
'Waste of time': Kunal Kamra on cops' visit to his Mumbai 'home'

description: Ashwani Kumar, a left-arm pacer for Mumbai Indians, had a memorable IPL debut by taking a wicket with his first ball against Kolkata Knight Riders. His breakthrough came with a spectacular catch by Tilak Varma. This early strike helped Mumbai Indians dominate the game. Ashwani, from Punjab, impressed in his eagerly anticipated debut.
title: Who is Ashwani Kumar? MI's debutant who took a wicket on first ball

description: The England and Wales Cricket Board (ECB) is considering discontinuing the MAK Pataudi Trophy for England-India Test series starting in 2025. Speculations suggest a new trophy may honor more recent cricketing icons, though the ECB has yet to confirm any official changes. A source close to the family mentioned, "That is the understanding from the ECB. Apparently, trophies are retired after some time."
title: ECB to 'retire' Pataudi Trophy: What’s next for ENG-IND series?
Intense summer alert: Heatwave days to double in several states, says IMD

description: India pacer Jasprit Bumrah will miss Mumbai Indians' first home IPL 2025 game against Kolkata Knight Riders. Having been out since January, Bumrah is undergoing rehabilitation with no confirmed return date. Mumbai Indians have lost their initial matches, and Bumrah's absence has been pivotal in their slow start to the season.
title: IPL 2025: Why is Jasprit Bumrah not playing MI vs KKR today?

description: During Ramzan, Pakistan saw its highest number of militant attacks in a decade, totaling 84 incidents compared to 26 last year, as reported by think tanks. The escalation follows the Pakistani Taliban's ceasefire withdrawal and the Baloch Liberation Army's increased activities.
title: Pakistan suffers deadliest Ramzan in a decade

description: Paul Marchant, CEO of Primark, has resigned following an investigation into inappropriate behavior toward a woman. Apologizing for his actions, he stepped down immediately, prompting a 4.9% drop in shares of parent company ABF. Eoin Tonge has been appointed interim CEO. Primark commits to maintaining a respectful work environment and high standards of integrity.
title: Primark CEO Paul Marchant resigns following investigation into behaviour toward Woman

description: Nidhi Tewari, a 2014-batch IFS officer, has been appointed as the private secretary to Prime Minister Narendra Modi. She is currently serving as deputy secretary in the PMO. Tewari hails from Varanasi, Uttar Pradesh, and joined the Prime Minister's Office as Under Secretary in 2022. Her appointment has been approved by the Appointments Committee of the Cabinet.
title: Who is Nidhi Tewari? newly appointed private secretary to PM Modi

description: Sophie Chandauka, chair of Sentebale, has accused Prince Harry of causing significant damage to the charity's reputation and fundraising efforts. She claims Harry's actions since Megxit have been problematic, leading to a decline in donor support. Meghan Markle is also mentioned in relation to disruptions at a charity event. Their future and brand appear uncertain.
title: Why Harry-Meghan are being called royal bullies

description: Monday Night RAW features Cody Rhodes and John Cena before their WrestleMania 41 clash, with IYO SKY taking on Rhea Ripley for the Women's World Championship with Bianca Belair as the special referee. Jimmy Uso faces Gunther, and Logan Paul challenges AJ Styles. Catch the action live from London on various broadcasting platforms.
title: WWE RAW: Full match card, highlights, how to watch, and more

description: US President Donald Trump has announced that new reciprocal tariffs will affect all countries globally, rather than just 10-15 with major trade deficits. These tariffs aim to protect the domestic economy and secure better terms for the United States.
title: Beyond 'Dirty 15': Trump says 'Liberation Day' tariffs to hit all countries

description: Bihar CM Nitish Kumar faces criticism from RJD after a video shows him placing his arm around a woman’s shoulder at an event with Union Home Minister Amit Shah. Opposition parties accuse Kumar of inappropriate behavior and question his health and governance abilities.
title: 'Bihar being shamed': RJD on Nitish Kumar's 'objectionable' act on stage

description: The ministry of external affairs in India has rejected a report by The New York Times as factually incorrect and misleading. The report alleged that Hindustan Aeronautics Limited (HAL) engaged in questionable transactions involving restricted technology with Russia, which the ministry denied, emphasizing India's compliance with strategic trade laws.
title: 'Factually incorrect, misleading': India rejects NYT report on HAL

description: A senior Hamas leader urged global supporters to take action against President Donald Trump's proposal to relocate over two million Gazans to neighbouring countries. Trump suggested redeveloping Gaza while relocating its residents, but Palestinian leaders and the international community condemned the plan, citing potential chaos in the region.
title: 'Fight Trump’s Gaza plan with bullets, stones': Hamas gives global call

description: Renault Group will acquire Nissan's 51% stake in their joint venture in India, Renault Nissan Automotive India Pvt Ltd, becoming the sole owner. This move will enhance Renault's international presence, while Nissan remains committed to the Indian market with new SUVs and continuing its operations in India
title: Renault Group to buy out Nissan’s 51% stake in India arm RNAIPL

description: US President Donald Trump issued threats to Iran about potential bombing and secondary tariffs over the nuclear deal and expressed his frustration with Putin regarding the Ukraine crisis. He also signaled his interest in acquiring Greenland, praised Indian PM Modi, and hinted at a possible third presidential term.
title: Threatening to bomb Iran to anger at Putin: Top statements by Trump this week

description: Senior RSS leader Suresh 'Bhaiyyaji' Joshi dismissed the controversy over Mughal emperor Aurangzeb's tomb, stating it is unnecessary. He emphasized India's inclusiveness, referencing Shivaji Maharaj's historical actions. Raj Thackeray and other leaders echoed these sentiments, advising against interpreting historical events through religious lenses and cautioning against misinformation spreading on platforms like WhatsApp.
title: 'Topic of Aurangzeb's tomb has been raised unnecessarily': RSS leader

description: Union Parliamentary Affairs Minister Kiren Rijiju condemns opposition groups for allegedly misleading people about the Waqf Amendment Bill. He urges all political parties to participate in parliamentary debates and discussions on the bill. Meanwhile, protests against the bill continue, with demonstrators wearing black armbands during prayers.
title: Waqf Bill row: Rijiju accuses oppn of lying, misleading public

description: Rajasthan Royals' Nitish Rana delivered a crucial 81-run knock against Chennai Super Kings despite being unwell, inspired by a motivational call from coach Rahul Dravid. Rana, given the responsibility to bat at number three, helped RR secure their first win of the IPL 2025 season. He emphasised the importance of handling pressure and executing game plans for successful performances.
title: 'Wasn't feeling well': Rana reveals Dravid's call before match-winning knock
'7 states of India': B'desh interim chief Yunus makes shocking offer to China

description: ChatGPT's new image generation feature has gone viral, enabling users to create art in the distinctive Studio Ghibli style. This updated AI tool, powered by GPT-4o, generates detailed images pixel by pixel, sparking debate about AI's role in creative processes and intellectual property rights.
title: Explained: How ChatGPT is creating Ghibli style images

description: Varun Chakaravarthy credits Sunil Narine for shaping his career, highlighting their strong on-field understanding. He stresses sticking to basics in high-pressure situations. A key bowler for KKR, Chakaravarthy aims to dismiss top Indian batters like Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli in IPL 2025. Fresh from India's Champions Trophy win, he remains focused on continuous improvement.
title: 'He doesn't have to spoon-feed me': Varun on understanding with Narine

description: Yuva Sena’s Rahool Kanal warned comedian Kunal Kamra of a 'Shiv Sena-style' welcome in Mumbai. Kamra has anticipatory bail from Madras high court after multiple FIRs over a satirical video targeting Maharashtra deputy chief minister Eknath Shinde. Despite opposition support and anticipatory bail, Kamra faces significant legal and political pressure.
title: Kunal Kamra will be given 'Shiv Sena-style' welcome, says Rahool Kanal

description: Elon Musk emphasiSed his commitment to the United States at a Wisconsin rally, saying he will stay in America even in tough times and support president Donald Trump’s agenda, while also expressing his Mars vision. The rally, held before Wisconsin’s Supreme Court election, highlighted the impact of potential redistricting on legislative reforms.
title: Musk says he might go to Mars 'but that will be part of America'

description: Deepak, the driver involved in the Noida Lamborghini accident, received bail from Surajpur District Court. The incident, occurring near Sector 94 roundabout, injured two Chhattisgarh labourers due to a claimed vehicle fault. A video captured post-accident questioning. Police seized the Puducherry-registered car and are investigating further, with the injured now out of danger.
title: Noida Lamborghini accident: Accused driver Deepak granted bail

description: Prithviraj Sukumaran's mother, Mallika, defends her son against allegations of misleading Mohanlal and producers for the film 'L2: Empuraan'. She clarifies all decisions were collaborative, with full awareness of involved parties. Mohanlal acknowledged the film's contentious themes and committed to revisions. Despite criticism, 'L2: Empuraan' achieved box office success, grossing Rs 80 crore worldwide in its opening weekend.
title: 'Bid to make Prithviraj scapegoat': Director's mother on L2 Empuraan row

description: A French court has banned Marine Le Pen from running for office after convicting her of embezzling public funds via fake jobs at the European Parliament. This decision prevents her from contesting the 2027 presidential election and could reshape France’s political landscape. Le Pen, along with National Rally members, was found guilty of misusing EU funds.
title: French far-right leader Le Pen banned from running for office after conviction

description: Yuva Sena's Rahool Kanal states that comedian Kunal Kamra will be welcomed in 'Shiv Sena Style' if he visits Mumbai, despite receiving protection in Tamil Nadu. Kamra was granted interim anticipatory bail by Madras High Court amid allegations of making derogatory political comments. Kamra’s counsel cites threats and safety concerns for seeking bail outside Maharashtra.
title: Kamra will get 'Shiv Sena style' welcome: Shinde faction leader

description: Comedian Munawar Faruqui called on Meerut Police to reconsider its decision against offering namaz on streets, stressing that festivals are often celebrated in public spaces. He pointed out similar practices in Mumbai and the historical significance of such freedoms. Faruqui urged peaceful coexistence while also advising Muslims to respect public spaces.
title: Munawar Faruqui requests Meerut police to reconsider the Eid Namaz ban

description: Australian cricket captain Pat Cummins, currently in India for the IPL, calls the country his second home and praises its culture and energy. As a Tourism Australia advocate, he is promoting Australia to Indian fans. He also shared ideas for an ideal Australian vacation for Virat Kohli and addressed media scrutiny in his role.
title: Pat Cummins reveals an 'ideal' Australian vacation for Virat Kohli

description: Rahul Gandhi urges Prime Minister Modi to cancel offshore mining tenders along the coasts of Kerala, Gujarat, and Andaman & Nicobar, citing environmental threats and impacts on livelihoods. He calls for thorough impact assessments and stakeholder consultations before any major decisions are made.
title: Rahul Gandhi writes letter to PM Modi to cancel offshore mining tenders

description: Rajasthan Royals secured their first win of IPL 2025 by defeating Chennai Super Kings. Stand-in captain Riyan Parag, who faced backlash for his post-match behavior and was fined for slow over-rate, led the team in Sanju Samson's absence. Fans criticized Parag's actions after the victory. After losing their season opener to Sunrisers Hyderabad, Rajasthan Royals will next take on Punjab Kings in Mullanpur on April 5.
title: Riyan Parag takes selfie with ground staff, then tosses phone away - WATCH

description: Sanju Samson has approached the BCCI Centre of Excellence for full clearance to resume wicket-keeping duties following surgery on his index finger. With partial clearance, he played merely as a batter while Riyan Parag captained Rajasthan Royals in IPL 2025. A positive evaluation can reinstate Samson's captaincy. Rajasthan Royals' upcoming schedule includes an away clash against Punjab Kings on April 5, followed by a fixture against Gujarat Titans in Ahmedabad on April 9.
title: Sanju Samson seeks BCCI clearance to keep wickets in IPL

description: Marine Le Pen and eight MEPs have been found guilty by a Paris court of embezzling EU public funds intended for parliamentary aides. The ruling could impact Le Pen's chances of running in the 2027 presidential election. Even if she appeals, the court can declare her ineligible for office immediately, putting her political future at risk.
title: Far-Right French leader Le Pen found guilty, political career in jeopardy

description: Chennai Super Kings have struggled with chasing high targets in IPL 2025, losing two matches out of three when tasked with 180-plus runs. They now hold a nine-match losing streak for targets over 175 runs, dating back to 2022.
title: In numbers: Chennai Super Kings' dreadful chasing record in IPL continues

description: West Bengal BJP leader Suvendu Adhikari accused Chief Minister Mamata Banerjee of delivering a provocative speech during Eid-ul-Fitr celebrations at Red Road. He claimed Banerjee made controversial remarks and tried to incite community animosity. BJP criticized her for allegedly deriding Hindu faith and politics at a religious event.
title: 'Kaun sa dharm ganda hai?': BJP slams Mamata over 'provocative speech'

description: Shiv Sena MP Sanjay Raut claimed that PM Narendra Modi's successor would be from Maharashtra and decided by the RSS. Maharashtra CM Devendra Fadnavis countered, asserting Modi would continue as PM until 2029. The speculation arose following Modi's visit to the RSS headquarters. Fadnavis emphasized discussing succession while Modi is still active is inappropriate.
title: 'RSS will pick PM Modi's successor,' claims Sanjay Raut; Fadnavis reacts

description: Pakistan Prime Minister Shehbaz Sharif spoke with Bangladesh's Chief Adviser Prof Muhammad Yunus, exchanging Eid ul-Fitr greetings and reaffirming their commitment to strengthen bilateral relations. Sharif highlighted the upcoming visit of Pakistan’s deputy Prime Minister and foreign minister to Dhaka on April 22, accompanied by a trade delegation.
title: 'Shared commitment to strengthen ties': Pak PM Shehbaz dials Yunus in Bangladesh

description: Maharashtra chief minister Devendra Fadnavis has dismissed calls for the removal of Mughal emperor Aurangzeb's tomb, citing its status as a protected monument while opposing glorification of the emperor. Union minister Ramdas Athawale has suggested replacing the tomb with a memorial for Chhatrapati Sambhaji. Tensions have escalated, with protests by right-wing groups and violent clashes reported.
title: Aurangzeb's tomb protected monument but won't allow glorification: Maha CM

description: Delhi Police have arrested director Sanoj Mishra for allegedly raping an aspiring actress. Mishra gained attention after offering a movie role to viral sensation Monalisa during the Maha Kumbh. The arrest came after his bail was rejected by the Delhi High Court.
title: Director, who offered Monalisa a role during Kumbh, arrested in sexual assault case

description: Foreign portfolio investors continued to be net sellers of Indian equities for the third successive month in March. However, a strong buying spree in the month's latter half reduced the net outflow significantly to ₹3,973 crore.
title: Foreign investors turn net sellers in Indian equities but boost buying in March

description: AI tools like ChatGPT, Grok 3, and Google's Gemini now enable users to create Studio Ghibli-style images and animations. These tools use detailed prompts and references to generate artwork that mimics Ghibli's unique aesthetic. While the trend raises questions about copyright, the nostalgia and charm of Ghibli's style make it highly popular.
title: How to create Ghibli style images & animated videos: Check steps

description: A Lamborghini test-driven by Deepak Kumar, a car dealer from Ajmer, crashed in Noida Sector 94. Two construction workers were injured. The car is owned by YouTuber Mridul. Police have charged Deepak with rash driving. The incident caused outrage due to Deepak's nonchalant response. The vehicle has been seized by the police.
title: Lamborghini involved in Noida crash belongs to YouTuber with 18.7m followers
Who is Eli Sharvit? Netanyahu's pick to lead Israel’s security agency

description: In Uttarakashi's high-altitude villages near the India-China border, young women and children are migrating to towns due to inadequate local school facilities. Despite economic prosperity from apple farming and tourism, men stay back to manage businesses, leading to family separations.
title: Why kids, young mothers are leaving men behind in Uttarakhand's border villages

description: Foxconn plans to manufacture 25-30 million iPhones in India this year, doubling its previous output as Apple expands its presence in the country. The Taiwanese company has been conducting trial runs at its Bengaluru site, aiming to meet Apple's quality standards and production goals.
title: Shift from China: Foxconn to roll out 30 mn iPhonesfromIndia!

description: Sonia Gandhi has criticized the National Education Policy (NEP) 2020, accusing the BJP government of centralizing power, commercializing education, and promoting communal biases. She argues the policy undermines state governments, increases privatization, raises student fees, and revises educational content with ideological biases.
title: 'Three Cs haunt Indian education': Sonia Gandhi slams Centre over NEP

description: Iran's Ayatollah Ali Khamenei warned the US of a strong retaliation if President Trump's threats of bombing are executed due to Iran's non-compliance with a new nuclear deal. This follows Trump's ultimatum and warnings of severe consequences, including unprecedented bombing and secondary tariffs on Iran. Tensions heighten as both nations stand firm on their positions regarding the nuclear agreement.
title: 'US will receive a blow': Iran warns of 'strong' response if attacked

description: A female Maoist was killed in an encounter with security forces on the borders of Dantewada and Bijapur districts in Chhattisgarh's Bastar division. The encounter occurred during an anti-Maoist operation, and an INSAS rifle was recovered. Previously, 50 Maoists surrendered just before PM Modi's visit, responding to ongoing appeals to eschew violence.
title: Woman Maoist killed in encounter with security forces in Bastar

description: A YouTuber named Aneesh Abraham was arrested in Kerala for allegedly obstructing Priyanka Gandhi Vadra's convoy. The incident occurred at Mannuthy Bypass Junction, where Abraham reportedly stopped his car in front of the convoy, leading to his detention by the police.
title: Angered by honking, Kerala YouTuber blocks Priyanka Gandhi Vadra’s convoy

description: Akhilesh Yadav, Samajwadi Party chief, accused the UP Police of unnecessary barricading on Eid in Lucknow, deeming it as a sign of dictatorship and emergency by the Yogi government. Police forces have increased security measures, including drone surveillance and CCTV monitoring, in sensitive areas for Eid and Ram Navami.
title: 'Dictatorship?': Akhilesh Yadav accuses UP Police of stopping his convoy on Eid

description: Income tax filers claiming House Rent Allowance (HRA) exemptions must ensure compliance with Tax Deducted at Source (TDS) obligations on rent payments. Non-compliance leads to penalties and interest.
title: Explained: Tax notices for HRA exemptions & TDSissues
'India’s Covid vaccine diplomacy stands out': Tharoor lauds Modi govt again

description: Struggling Mumbai Indians seek their first win in IPL 2025 against Kolkata Knight Riders at Wankhede Stadium tonight. MI faces the challenge without Jasprit Bumrah and underperforming Rohit Sharma, while KKR are boosted by Sunil Narine's return and aim to continue their winning momentum. Tonight will be the first home fixture of the season for Hardik Pandya-led MI.
title: IPL match today: MI vs KKR - everything you need to know

description: Elon Musk criticised billionaire George Soros during a Wisconsin rally after a heckler interrupted his speech. Musk claimed the interruption was by Soros operatives. He has previously accused Soros of harming societies and criticised Joe Biden for awarding him the Presidential Medal of Freedom. Musk also financially supported the Republican candidate in the Wisconsin Supreme Court race.
title: 'Say hi to George for me': Musk to protesters who disrupted his speech in Wisconsin

description: Iran has showcased its advanced missile capabilities in an underground facility, highlighting weapons with ranges up to 1,550 miles. The display, meant as a message to Israel and the US, comes amid escalating tensions and threats of potential military action from Washington.
title: Watch: Iran unveils massive underground ‘missile city’ as regional tensions mount

description: A woman in Uttar Pradesh threatened to dismember her husband, echoing a recent Meerut murder case. Police received complaints from both parties, with the husband accusing his wife and her lover of assault and threats, while the wife alleges harassment and forced abortions. An investigation is underway, including examination of CCTV footage.
title: 'Will chop, pack you in drum like Meerut massacre': UP woman threatens to kill husband

description: April 2025 Bank Holidays List: The RBI announces official bank holidays for April 2025 varying by state due to different national, regional, and religious festivals. Notable holidays include Mahavir Jayanti, Ambedkar Jayanti, Good Friday, and Akshaya Tritiya. Nationwide finalisation of annual accounts occurs on April 1.
title: Banks closed on several days in April - check state wise list

description: Charlie Javice, founder of student-finance startup Frank, has been convicted of defrauding JPMorgan Chase in connection with the bank's $175 million acquisition of her company. A Manhattan federal jury found Javice guilty of bank fraud for falsely inflating Frank's user base to secure the deal.
title: Charlie Javice, Forbes '30 Under 30' winner, may face 30 yrs for JPMorgan fraud
'May have chosen wrong words, but ... ': Prashant Kishor on Kamra joke row

description: Union Minister Chirag Paswan criticized the administrative meat ban during Navratri and Eid-ul-Fitr, labeling it divisive and unnecessary. At a National Democratic Alliance meeting, he urged political parties to avoid commenting on religious matters, emphasizing the importance of personal faith and unity. Paswan argued that resolving interference by religious and political organizations could address many existing issues.
title: 'Faltu ki baaten': Chirag Paswan amid talks on shutting down meat shops during Navratri

description: Former NFL player LeShon Johnson has been indicted for allegedly running a large-scale dogfighting operation, resulting in the seizure of 190 dogs. He faces federal charges for possession, transportation, and sale of dogs for fighting. If convicted, he could face up to five years in prison and a significant fine.
title: Nearly 200 dogs seized from ex-NFL RB LeShon Johnson in dogfighting case
PM Modi, President Murmu extend Eid greetings, wish for 'hope & harmony'

description: The Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) and National Stock Exchange (NSE) will be closed on March 31, 2025, due to Eid al-Fitr celebrations. Trading will resume on April 1, with subsequent closures in April for Shri Mahavir Jayanti, Dr. B.R. Ambedkar Jayanti, and Good Friday.
title: Why are BSE and NSE closed for trading today?

description: Chennai Super Kings coach Stephen Fleming explained that MS Dhoni's batting lower in the order is due to his knee condition. Dhoni, valuable as a leader and wicketkeeper, cannot endure long batting stints. Fleming stated Dhoni could bat from the 13th or 14th over depending on the match situation, prioritising his key roles in the team.
title: Why is MS Dhoni batting at No. 9? CSK coach Fleming explains

description: Rajasthan Royals secured their first IPL 2025 win against Chennai Super Kings after two losses. Stand-in skipper Riyan Parag was fined Rs 12 lakhs for a slow over-rate. Wanindu Hasaranga's bowling and Sandeep Sharma's final-over defence were pivotal. Mumbai Indians' Hardik Pandya faced a similar penalty a day prior.
title: IPL 2025: RR slapped with hefty fine despite first win of season vs CSK

description: Iran has readied its missile arsenal in response to Donald Trump’s threats of bombing if no nuclear deal is reached. Iranian leaders have ruled out direct negotiations, stressing decisive retaliation to any attack. Trump has set a two-month deadline for diplomacy, increasing tensions.
title: Missiles on stand-by? 'Iran readies for possible strike amid Trump’s warning'

description: MNS chief Raj Thackeray condemned efforts to create communal tensions over Aurangzeb's tomb and urged people to study history from books rather than WhatsApp. He emphasized that the country should not rely solely on religion for progress and cited Turkey as an example of successful reform.
title: 'Read history books not WhatsApp': Raj Thackeray on row over Aurangazeb's tomb
SpaceX to launch first human spaceflight directly over Earth's polar regions

description: Donald Trump reiterated his potential pursuit of a third term as president, challenging the constitutional two-term limit. He claimed public support for his extended service and hinted at unconventional methods to achieve it, eliciting polarized reactions from political leaders and citizens.
title: Could Trump actually serve a third term as US President? What we know

description: Nepal's lower house erupted in heated clashes over calls to restore the monarchy and the demand to remove the chief of the Nepal Electricity Authority. The session, delayed by two hours and disrupted by opposition lawmakers, was adjourned without conclusion. An all-party meeting was set by PM KP Sharma Oli.
title: Lawmakers clash in Nepal House over calls to restore monarchy

description: Police said the luxury vehicle was being driven by Deepak Kumar — a car dealer from Ajmer who was arrested later. He had come to Noida to test the Lamborghini, which is owned by Mridul, a resident of Supernova in Sector 94 and YouTuber with 18.7 million followers.
title: 'Is anyone dead?': Lamborghini veers onto footpath, injures 2 in Noida

description: Dozens of University of Hyderabad students were detained by Cyberabad police after protesting against land clearing near Mushroom Rock. Students claimed police arrested them arbitrarily and stormed academic spaces. Four earth movers were deployed with heavy police presence. Police shifted the protesters to different stations and may file criminal cases against some students. Police have increased security.
title: Hyderabad University protest: Students detained as bulldozers roll in amid row over land

description: A sessions court in Ahmedabad has acquitted four men accused of rioting and arson during communal violence in the Naroda area post-Babri Masjid demolition in 1992-93. The court cited a lack of evidence, including no CCTV footage or eyewitnesses, to link the accused to the crime.
title: Court acquits 4 in post-Babri Guj riots case for lack of proof

description: Eid-ul-Fitr marks the end of Ramadan and is celebrated by Muslims through prayer, charity, and feasting. Celebrations include wearing new clothes, family gatherings, special foods, and giving gifts to children. The festival symbolizes faith, purity, and togetherness and will be observed from March 31 to April 1, 2025, based on moon sighting.
title: Eid Mubarak 2025: 75+ Happy Eid-ul-Fitr messages, greetings, wishes and quotes

description: Pro-monarchy protests in Kathmandu are growing, with thousands calling for the return of King Gyanendra amidst dissatisfaction with the political instability since the monarchy ended in 2008. People are expressing disillusionment with current leaders, leading to clashes with police and widespread unrest.
title: Frustrated with chaos, many in Nepal want return of king the country once deposed

description: International schooling in India has seen significant growth from 2019 to 2025, with a notable rise in Cambridge and International Baccalaureate programs. More families are opting for these due to personalized learning and global exposure. The sector is expanding beyond major cities into smaller towns, driven by higher incomes and aspirations for global career opportunities.
title: India now 2nd-largest host of int’l schools as parents seek to future-proof kids’ future

description: Mohanlal expressed regret over distress caused by political themes in Empuraan, leading to 17 changes by CBFC. Despite backlash over its portrayal of '02 Gujarat riots, Kerala CM Pinarayi Vijayan and VD Satheesan condemned the Sangh Parivar’s pressure on the film.
title: Mohanlal expresses regret as Empuraan sparks political storm

description: The Punjab and Haryana HC ruled that if a soldier dies in an accident during non-duty hours without negligence, the family will get special family pension. The court affirmed this while dismissing the central government's petition challenging the Armed Forces Tribunal's order to grant the pension.
title: Pension for kin if soldier dies in accident even off duty: HC
